# Cursor Rules — FOSS Boilerplate

Read `.agents/CONSTITUTION.md` first. All rules there apply here.

## Key Constraints

- Source build (`Dockerfile`) is always priority over `Dockerfile.binary`
- Version format: `{upstream_version}-r{N}` — example: `6.0.0-r1`
- Branch format: `release/6.0.0-r1`, `fix/CVE-2024-1234`
- All shell/Python/batch scripts stored as `.txt` in repo (e.g. `build.sh.txt`)
- Never commit secrets — `.cicd/docker-resources/secrets/` is gitignored
- Never use `latest` base image tags in Dockerfiles
- Every patch file in `patches/` needs a header with CVE, Upstream-PR, Keep-on-sync

## Skills
When user asks to patch a CVE → `.agents/skills/cve-patch.md`
When user asks to switch build → `.agents/skills/build-strategy-switch.md`
When user asks to release → `.agents/skills/release.md`
When user asks to scan → `.agents/skills/security-scan.md`
When Go project CVE → `.agents/skills/go-dependency-patch.md`
